    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Sussex County was formed in 1753 from Surry County.      
</p>
      <p>The deed books of Sussex County in this collection were created by the County Court.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Deed Books, 1754-1786, of Sussex County Court. The deed books record the name of the grantor and grantee, the residence of both individuals and the description of property being sold or transferred.  Deed Book C contains land titles.  The volumes have indexes which contains the first and last names of both parties.  It is arranged alphabetically from A-Z.  
</p>
    </scopecontent>
